Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.27,0:00:06.06,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Song by Matsuhashi Miki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.77,0:00:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reasoning and hints are interlinked,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.35,0:00:06.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allowing us to understand a case's mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.36,0:00:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today we return to Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an exciting case at "K3"!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.40,0:00:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that single truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.94,0:00:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.74,0:00:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.95,0:00:17.78,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,Something's just not right
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.41,0:00:21.91,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,nani wo motometeru no
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.41,0:00:26.63,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,uso ni nareteyuku kyou mo fake your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.38,0:00:32.67,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,The start of a century
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.97,0:00:36.14,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,tashika na mono nakute
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.14,0:00:41.22,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,hitori ja nakenai yowasa hate myself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:50.98,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,shinjiteru itami hikikae ni\Nkono mune umetsukushite
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:59.83,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,ima utsutte iru futari ga eranda michi kuru
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:03.45,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,I think it's only oh my destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.70,0:01:06.83,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,hate shinai yami no mukou ni
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.17,0:01:13.17,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,dare mo shiru koto no nai ashita ga aru
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.46,0:01:18.18,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,Oh yeah you're going nowhere it's only destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.43,0:01:21.47,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,ari no mama ni susunde
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.68,0:01:28.81,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,ima kanjite iru you're in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:32.82,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,You're in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.41,0:01:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A restaurant's opening party?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.70,0:01:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.37,0:01:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, my parents were the ones invited,\Nbut they both got colds and can't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.30,0:01:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I'm inviting you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.22,0:02:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I was saying, three of the most famous\NAmerican athletes will be here in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.43,0:02:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.31,0:02:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.98,0:02:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is this party?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.98,0:02:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.31,0:02:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's here in Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.07,0:02:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.28,0:02:18.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a unique opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.82,0:02:22.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I have some stuff to deal with here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.37,0:02:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.16,0:02:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome home...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.45,0:02:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, who're you talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.50,0:02:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just the professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.25,0:02:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to ask me about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.50,0:02:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.30,0:02:37.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.22,0:02:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's bad, I can call back later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.35,0:02:48.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we're good, we're good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.43,0:02:49.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.48,0:02:51.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you can't miss out on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.73,0:02:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those three famous athletes will be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.82,0:02:58.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pro-boxer Ricardo Barega,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.36,0:03:00.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Major Leaguer Mike Node,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:01.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And lastly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:13.75,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,The Osaka "3 K's" Case
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:13.75,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.01,0:03:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place has it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.05,0:03:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mai Kuraki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.97,0:03:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miho Komatsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.10,0:03:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,TWO-MIX!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.61,0:03:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my favorite...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.11,0:03:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okino Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.45,0:03:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so loud, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.49,0:03:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:49.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you the one carrying a picture around to get signed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.71,0:04:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is this really all right, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't have an invitation and we really weren't invited...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.76,0:04:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't worry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your Dad's famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.35,0:04:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.56,0:04:13.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.11,0:04:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.82,0:04:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been acting so strange lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.78,0:04:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.19,0:04:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hear him talking on the phone, saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.15,0:04:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Are you alone now?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"You haven't been exposed yet?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.62,0:04:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If it's bad, I'll call you back later."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.83,0:04:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.41,0:04:32.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-f-f-a-i-r.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.00,0:04:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must be attracted to some woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that maybe she asked him to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.59,0:04:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me. He's been talking to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.68,0:04:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.14,0:04:58.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please help me welcome the\Nowners of the World Restaurant, "K3".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.86,0:05:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're the special guests of tonight's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.03,0:05:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, we have the former world\Nheavyweight boxing champion,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.36,0:05:10.58,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Ricardo Barega\NFormer Boxer (36)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.82,0:05:09.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ricardo Barega{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.04,0:05:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next is the major leaguer who pitches 160km,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mike Node{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:19.96,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Mike Node\NMajor Leaguer (35)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.46,0:05:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And last up is the goalkeeper known\Nas the "Iron Wall of Europe",
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.76,0:05:27.13,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ray Curtis{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.13,0:05:30.35,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Ray Curtis\NPro Soccer Player (37)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.47,0:05:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.14,0:05:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.61,0:05:41.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? I told you this would be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.07,0:05:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll start with a few questions for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.15,0:05:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll ask why they chose Japan to open their restaurant in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.62,0:05:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you choose Japan to open your restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.54,0:06:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because Japan is like a second home to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.50,0:06:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He can speak Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.55,0:06:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My wife, and Mike's wife, are both Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ricardo just loves ninjas and samurais.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.44,0:06:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does the "K" in the restaurant's name, "K3", mean "Kings"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, that isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.11,0:06:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.99,0:06:29.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knockout.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.32,0:06:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "K" is from K.O.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:34.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.54,0:06:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strikeout, represented by a "K".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.87,0:06:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.67,0:06:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Goalkeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.04,0:06:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Keeper" begins with "K", doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:44.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.88,0:06:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, didn't you forget one, Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.22,0:06:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't Japan the home of your many scandals?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.44,0:07:02.69,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Ed McKay\NNews Reporter (48)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.02,0:07:02.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Maybe "K" stands for "kitanai".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.02,0:07:02.69,Signs,Note,0,0,0,,FILTH
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Ed, watch your language. Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mike, what'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.15,0:07:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, it's you who should watch your language.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm here by request, as I have my own invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.87,0:07:20.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, at least we're all friends here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.79,0:07:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I interviewed all of you fairly, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:28.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's famous in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.84,0:07:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a reporter that specializes in\Nexposing famous athletes' scandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:42.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He exposes them taking illegal drugs,\Nplaying fixed games, and having affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.31,0:07:46.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That somehow reminds me of Heiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.98,0:07:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.03,0:07:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.36,0:07:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well then, how about you all submit some questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.70,0:07:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does anyone out there have a question for these three?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.33,0:08:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does anyone have a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.88,0:08:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, the young woman in the back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.59,0:08:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come up to the stage now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.89,0:08:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.10,0:08:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please ask your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, I actually have a request...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you please sign this, Mr. Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.28,0:08:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.62,0:08:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They can't, they didn't come to sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.70,0:08:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You helped relax this party.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll think of this as a present.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.05,0:08:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, how about on this uniform?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will this do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.68,0:08:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.68,0:09:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't, these are the prizes for the guests...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.39,0:09:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.27,0:09:04.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have three more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.81,0:09:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you write a name, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK. Young lady, your name is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shinichi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.65,0:09:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please write "To Shinichi" on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.03,0:09:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.78,0:09:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.58,0:09:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She... remembered...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.79,0:09:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I was a fan of Ray...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.50,0:09:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.04,0:09:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember to call her soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:34.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.84,0:09:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.05,0:09:41.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually goalkeepers are #1, right? He's #8.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.64,0:09:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because Ray used to be a fielder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.56,0:09:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But during the World Cup, both the first string and back-up\Ngoalkeepers were injured, putting them in a pinch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.15,0:09:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They decided to make Ray the goalkeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.40,0:09:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His super-saves led them to victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.49,0:10:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, when he entered the Sevilla League in\NSpain, he came on as a goalkeeper with the #8.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.46,0:10:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, he wears it for his Major\NLeague Soccer team as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.79,0:10:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what does that #99 mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.42,0:10:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know he's a pitcher, but are there 99 people on the team?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.01,0:10:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That stands for 99mph, which is 160km in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.72,0:10:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the speed of his pitch, so he requested that number.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that "4"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.44,0:10:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the boxing gloves, right under his signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.86,0:10:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because Ricardo used to always win in four rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, he started putting it under his signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.66,0:10:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.45,0:10:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should've studied up before coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.17,0:10:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.67,0:10:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should be more interested in their phone\Nnumbers than their uniform numbers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.75,0:10:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.92,0:10:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.05,0:10:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:05.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, did that brat have you do this for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.22,0:11:06.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.52,0:11:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.60,0:11:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.73,0:11:15.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a ticket to the exhibition match in\NNagai that Mr. Ray will be playing in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.23,0:11:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.40,0:11:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.53,0:11:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.11,0:11:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, he's pretty generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.99,0:11:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They did ask me to do something in return though...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.12,0:11:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A transceiver?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.83,0:11:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was a bit surprised when they asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.30,0:11:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ray, you're OK. Switch it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.97,0:11:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ricardo, that's not it. To the left, the left!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.93,0:11:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.01,0:11:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're using the hotel rooms above\Nthe restaurant to form a "K".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.15,0:11:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, when the guests come out, they'll be surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:12:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why are they doing this themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They planned for them to do it themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If one of them were to come out, it'd be chaotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.29,0:12:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why they got us to look over the "K" for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.04,0:12:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, the lights from the earlier rooms are on, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.80,0:12:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The light on the first floor, at the end of the "K", is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.92,0:12:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK. I'm on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.09,0:12:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mike, please... um, "open", the curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.56,0:12:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.02,0:12:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.10,0:12:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're OK, too, Mr. Ricardo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.69,0:12:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.90,0:12:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, is it on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.61,0:12:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.07,0:12:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.15,0:12:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "K" is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.70,0:12:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That glass window...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.24,0:12:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a gunshot!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.33,0:12:55.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.92,0:12:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:12:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that a shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.34,0:13:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, make sure those three stay in their rooms!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:08.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, don't go alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.32,0:13:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.98,0:13:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.87,0:13:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that reporter from earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.91,0:13:34.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably shot by this gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.04,0:13:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His hand is latched onto something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.29,0:13:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-His belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.18,0:13:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That glass window...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.76,0:13:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a gunshot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.98,0:13:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.73,0:14:00.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, make sure they stay in their rooms!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.98,0:14:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.41,0:14:12.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that reporter from earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.70,0:14:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably shot by this gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.71,0:14:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His hand is latched onto something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.46,0:14:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-His belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.13,0:14:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is a 48-years old male from\NChicago, America, named Ed McKay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:36.31,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Inspector Ohtaki\NOsaka Police Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:35.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The cause of death was a gunshot wound to the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weapon was this Smith & Wesson revolver.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.77,0:14:46.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the blood stains, death wasn't instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.28,0:14:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, do you remember when the shot was fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.62,0:14:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, around 8:05 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was outside of the hotel with Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.50,0:15:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw the glass break, without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.42,0:15:04.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Outside of the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.29,0:15:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you about to go into the party?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.50,0:15:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.96,0:15:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those three asked us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.84,0:15:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To look at the "K" above the restaurant...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.39,0:15:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make sure it was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.06,0:15:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Those" three?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:22.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I mean the owners of the "K3" restaurant...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The former pro-boxer, Ricardo Barega...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Major Leaguer, Mike Node...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.90,0:15:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And pro-soccer player, Ray Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.36,0:15:34.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, those three were responsible for turning the lights on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.20,0:15:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.62,0:15:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ray was responsible for the 1st and 2nd floors...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.50,0:15:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mike was responsible for the 3rd and 4th floors...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.37,0:15:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ricardo was responsible for the fifth floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.59,0:15:46.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those three did it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.59,0:15:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means any of those three could've committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.18,0:15:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from their pasts, all three of them have motives.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.22,0:15:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.39,0:16:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The glass window that broke was\Nin the middle of the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.94,0:16:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, they were all in their rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.56,0:16:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.32,0:16:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know what rooms they were in at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.95,0:16:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember Mr. Mike was in the room above\Nthe crime scene opening the curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.08,0:16:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know Mr. Ricardo had the wrong\Nlight on in one of the rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.62,0:16:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after he fixed it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.62,0:16:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ray went to turn on the light he\Nhad forgotten on the bottom floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.42,0:16:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And right when the "K" was completed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.13,0:16:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the gunshot broke the glass window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.76,0:16:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see any of them at that exact moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.64,0:16:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.72,0:16:44.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I did see the lights go off after Mr. Mike\Nopened the curtains, and Mr. Ray's a bit later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About three seconds later, the gun was fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.86,0:16:53.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after that, they all looked out the\Nwindows and asked what was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.45,0:16:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, just who is the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:17:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe a guest from the restaurant did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, when it happened, Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} and I rushed up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.42,0:17:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer was one of those that came up with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.05,0:17:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could have escaped then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.76,0:17:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that mean all of the guests are suspects?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.26,0:17:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's too many people to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.22,0:17:23.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.48,0:17:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this man's left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.02,0:17:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's he holding on to?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.48,0:17:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-His belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.03,0:17:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And look at the fingers on his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.70,0:17:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His little finger and ring finger are curled in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he played Janken with the criminal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.74,0:17:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.24,0:17:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, does this mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:47.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.17,0:17:51.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grasping onto his belt and the position\Nof his fingers, they're his...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.92,0:17:53.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.84,0:17:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't necessarily mean it's about his belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:18:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may be about his pants, like maybe the belt\Nmeans it's something about that pair of pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.64,0:18:05.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were his pants, wouldn't his hands\Nbe on top of his pants, not his belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.61,0:18:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who uses their belt-line to take off their pants?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.03,0:18:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I guess we'll have to ask all of the guests downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.28,0:18:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.07,0:18:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That won't be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.74,0:18:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, the murderer is one of those three...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.50,0:18:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The belt...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.50,0:18:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the evidence is that the belt is worn by the champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.88,0:18:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! The criminal is the former\Nboxing champion, Ricardo Barega!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.22,0:18:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what about his fingers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.72,0:18:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Ricardo usually beats his opponents in\Nfour rounds, there should be four fingers out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.39,0:18:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, then it should be the pro-soccer player, Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.86,0:18:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did great in Spain, Italy, and America\Nand even played for their national teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.15,0:19:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ray also won a title while playing\Nin the English Premier League.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.57,0:19:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.32,0:19:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, if he means three fingers, in baseball you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.50,0:19:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, when a pitcher pitches, doesn't he use three fingers?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.54,0:19:13.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.25,0:19:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer is the Major Leaguer, Mike!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.92,0:19:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.38,0:19:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mike's team has never won a title.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.13,0:19:23.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, you don't win a belt in baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.39,0:19:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that eliminate soccer as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.89,0:19:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The keys to figuring this out are the three fingers on\Nthe right hand and the white bandou in his left.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.94,0:19:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll need to get past these before we can go further.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.98,0:19:37.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bandou?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.78,0:19:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? You don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.69,0:19:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Bandou" refers to a leather belt in the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.28,0:19:44.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy doesn't know western sayings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bandou... 3...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.12,0:19:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bandou... 3...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.16,0:19:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bandou 3...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bandou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.41,0:19:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.00,0:19:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Bandou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.79,0:20:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right! Check the guest registry for\Nanyone with the name "Bandou"!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.88,0:20:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.13,0:20:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this that "Sleeping Kogoro" guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.55,0:20:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's just a little drunk today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.43,0:20:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there's nothing else we can do\Nwith the dying message right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.23,0:20:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's wait until after the gun powder test.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.77,0:20:17.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.77,0:20:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll head on down and get the guests ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.19,0:20:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, don't forget those other three in their rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, thanks for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.38,0:20:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.26,0:20:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.80,0:20:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would your name happen to be Bandou?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.38,0:20:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.47,0:20:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well? Anything come up, Ohtaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-han{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.14,0:20:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.40,0:20:57.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about those three?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.15,0:21:01.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We tested them first, but nothing came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.53,0:21:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you searched them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.78,0:21:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just a light body-check.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.70,0:21:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their managers won't let us do anything more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.95,0:21:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earlier, didn't Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-han{\r} mention that\Nthose three weren't fond of the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.96,0:21:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy reported that Ricardo fought in\Nfixed matches and was forced to retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.89,0:21:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that Ray was kicked out of\NEuropean soccer for illegal drug abuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.89,0:21:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He claimed Mike had an affair that lead to his divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.35,0:21:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I heard that his wife was Japanese\Nand they're doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.02,0:21:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, it would seem that he\Nwasn't killed over the scandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.61,0:21:49.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, why do you think that isn't enough to kill?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because he just lost the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sued him for their innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.91,0:22:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those three may have disliked him,\Nbut not enough to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.54,0:22:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.09,0:22:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.85,0:22:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's... What's stopping you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:22.94,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,always
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:22.94,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Song by Mai Kuraki
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.40,0:22:33.66,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love, always give my love to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.66,0:22:38.83,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love, always give my love to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.04,0:22:47.09,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,son janai!? ima kara demo iin janai!? yareru koto
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.04,0:22:47.09,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Don't you think so?! From now on, let's... Isn't it great?! Do what we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.18,0:22:57.77,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,omotta toori ni yatte miyou kimi to deau made
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.18,0:22:57.77,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,With the way I feel now, I know I had nothing before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.27,0:23:04.44,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,nani mo nakatta keredo me wo tojite omou
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.27,0:23:04.44,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,But when I close my eyes and think...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:09.15,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,isshoni ikiru basho ga aru kara
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:09.15,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,I know there's a place we can live together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:15.66,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,always ai wo mune ni yuuki wo dashite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:15.66,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,There will always be love in my heart; I've built up courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.91,0:23:20.25,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,tatoe sore ga dame da to shitemo ne
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.91,0:23:20.25,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,To say something is impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:25.67,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,No sore dake ga jibun janai
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:25.67,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,No, that's not like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.80,0:23:31.22,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Yes kazamuki ga kawatta ima tobi datou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.80,0:23:31.22,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Yes, the wind has changed: Let's start now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.26,0:23:36.22,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love, always give my love to you! Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.22,0:23:43.65,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my, give my love...
